.certs/
# Ignore everything customers may drop in the root keys/ dir (Ed25519 pairs,
# private cosign keys, etc.) — a safety net against committing private material.
# A negation on a file requires first re-including the directory itself (git
# will not descend into an excluded dir), so we exclude keys/* (contents) rather
# than keys/ (the dir) and then exempt the one PUBLIC key we ship.
keys/*
# Exempt the Lucairn cosign PUBLIC key (B1 supply-chain provenance): the
# distributable public key customers use to verify image signatures
# (`bin/lucairn verify-images` / `cosign verify --key`). PUBLIC key only —
# never a private cosign key or its password.
!keys/lucairn-cosign.pub
# Exempt the per-release signed-image digest records (B1 supply-chain
# provenance). These are PUBLIC: each line is `<repo>:<tag> <sha256:digest>`,
# the authoritative set `bin/lucairn verify-images` verifies BY DIGEST. No
# private material — image digests are derivable from the public registry.
!keys/image-digests-*.txt
# Exempt the dashboard's API-key management template directory
# (Slice 5). The root `keys/` pattern excludes crypto material that
# customers may leave next to the kit (Ed25519 pairs, etc.); the
# dashboard's `views/templates/keys/` subdir is unrelated source
# code and must ship in the repo.
!apps/dashboard/internal/views/templates/keys/
!apps/dashboard/internal/views/templates/keys/**
.DS_Store
